{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"049520e2-d6d7-468c-a375-6c0fa11493be","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_yK8BDJQ2gybh5XgrOvgPon","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5f39779551a24715bf04084abbad29bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5f39779551a24715bf04084abbad29bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"bcb24822-a656-4312-8287-5ae1641790a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed earlier in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should be last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n\n\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":446,"requestId":"1C50:2ED258:B3D7F6:D09A48:69F3FA0C"},"id":"c645ec79-312a-47e7-b303-44e39aaec288","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:47.781Z","parentId":"a2f84dcf-d845-4be4-ba99-16ee2acd0f8d"}
